## Vendored Skills

One skill remains vendored, renamed with an `mp-` prefix to mark
provenance:

| Path | Upstream | Notes |
|------|----------|-------|
| `skills/mp-zoom-out/` | https://github.com/mattpocock/skills/tree/main/zoom-out | Verbatim content; directory + `name:` field renamed `zoom-out` → `mp-zoom-out`. |

Six previously vendored skills (`grill-me`, `tdd`, `ubiquitous-language`,
`improve-codebase-architecture`, `obsidian-vault`, `write-a-skill`) were
**removed** — globally installed equivalents (`grilling`, `tdd`,
`domain-modeling`, `codebase-design`, `obsidian-vault`, `write-a-skill`)
supersede them, and vendoring alongside the global copies produced
duplicates. Load-bearing content was inlined before removal:
`references/architecture-language.md` (from
`improve-codebase-architecture/LANGUAGE.md`) and the TDD/module rules
already inlined in `references/coding-standards.md` and
`references/plan-writing.md`. See `docs/skills-bundled.md`.

